{"id":"nexus-c43","title":"status bar telemetry via grpc for remote clients","description":"Send all telemetry needed to emulate the TUI status bar (agent dots, session count, uptime) via gRPC so remote clients (Mac TUI, future web) can render equivalent status bars","notes":"## Feasibility\n- All data already exists in proto (HealthResponse, SessionList)\n- Need GetHealth RPC or extend SessionList with uptime/connection state\n- TUI uptime currently computed client-side — remote needs agent-reported uptime\n- Complexity: small — wiring existing data, no new types\n- Touches: proto/nexus.proto, grpc.rs, api.rs, dashboard.rs, stream.rs\n## Account Telemetry\n- CC emits rate_limit_event in stream-json: utilization %, rateLimitType (seven_day), surpassedThreshold, isUsingOverage\n- Parser should capture these and surface in status bar: usage gauge (91% of 7-day cap), warning threshold indicator\n- Also capture from result events: total_cost_usd, model, duration_api_ms, service_tier\n- Could show: model name, cost-per-command, rate limit gauge alongside existing infra metrics","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"task","owner":"leo@leonardoacosta.dev","created_at":"2026-03-21T12:05:15.051221917-05:00","created_by":"leonardoacosta","updated_at":"2026-03-21T13:05:32.982735705-05:00","closed_at":"2026-03-21T13:05:32.982735705-05:00","close_reason":"promoted to feature","labels":["idea"]}
